It is difficult to override rules causing errors in `.mjs` (and presumably `.cjs`) files in projects, due to the use of `overrides` in the `recommended` config having a high specificity:

https://github.com/mysticatea/eslint-plugin-node/blob/v9.0.1/lib/configs/recommended.js#L13

This ESLint config will not work:

```json
{
  "plugins": ["node"],
  "extends": ["plugin:node/recommended"],
  "rules": {
    "node/no-missing-import": "off"
  }
}
```

You must use matching `overrides` for `.mjs`:

```json
{
  "plugins": ["node"],
  "extends": ["plugin:node/recommended"],
  "overrides": [
    {
      "files": ["*.mjs", ".*.mjs"],
      "rules": {
        "node/no-missing-import": "off"
      }
    }
  ]
}
```

Hello in the latest version of crafty (1.7.1) there is some issue with overriding linting rules, even after running the autofix command:

`npx crafty jsLint js/**/*.tsx js/**/*.ts --fix`


What we tried:
The `overrides`  configuration is not taken into account, for all the 3 different ways .  

**1st way** 

`eslint: {
    rules: {
      "@swissquote/swissquote/import/prefer-default-export": "warn"
    },
    overrides: {
      files: ["*.ts", "*.tsx"],
      rules: {
        "@swissquote/swissquote/@typescript-eslint/no-unused-vars": [
          "warn",
          {args: "none", vars: "local", ignoreRestSiblings: true}
        ],
        "@swissquote/swissquote/@typescript-eslint/no-use-before-define": "warn"
      }
    }
  }`

**2nd way** 

` eslint: {
    rules: {
      "@swissquote/swissquote/import/prefer-default-export": "warn",
      "@swissquote/swissquote/@typescript-eslint/no-use-before-define": "warn"
    }
  },`

**3rd way**

eslint: {
    rules: {
      "@swissquote/swissquote/import/prefer-default-export": "warn",
      "@swissquote/swissquote/@typescript-eslint/no-unused-vars": [
        "error",
        { args: "none", vars: "local", ignoreRestSiblings: true }
      ],
      "@swissquote/swissquote/@typescript-eslint/no-use-before-define": "warn"
    }`

Maybe a helpful observation: 
In the modules `@swissquote.eslint-plugin-swissquote/index.js` module there is an `overrides` object already hardcoded, so I think there is problem overriding this one.
